column1: Opportunity not getting Closed Lost
column2:
Steps:
1. Login with DSAdmn Id in Showroom 
2. Click on Opportunities (screen tab) 
3. Search with Opty Id 
4. Check Oppurtunites Sales Stage status, if it is below 02a pink form, please closed lost the Opty Id by selecting the lost reason.
5. If Lost Order Information not reflecting, please click on Show more.
6. If Sales Stage field is grey, please click on ?ReAssign? (view tab) 
7. Closed lost the Opty from drop down box (Error: If it is reflecting error as 3 Follow up is required) 
8. Click on Activities View Tab and Update 3 Follow Up activities status as Done 
9. In case of Dealer Sales Invoice has been created against Opty Id and If it is more than 1 month, then follow Invoice cancellation process.
10. If Invoice has been cancelled, then De-allocate the Chassis.
11. Cancel Payment Receipt 
12. Cancel Sales Order with cancellation reason 
13. Update Lost Order Information at Opty Screen (same as above).
14. If any issues raise the ticket.

column1: Capturing Prospects from Dealer PSF-Sales Desk (BU: TMCV, Roles: DCRE/DCRM)
column2:
Scenario 1:
Steps:
1. Login using DSalCRE credentials.
2. Goto sitemap and click on invoice.
3. Click on Dealer PSF Sales Assessment (view tab) and then Associate 
4. Click on New to update Template 
5. Create Prospect Tab will enable. Window will be opened for updating the details 
6. Click on Finish button 
7. CRE needs to assign to himself. Goto Site Map and then click Dealer Campaigns 
8. Click on Prospects 
9. Search the Dealer PSF - Sales in Prospect Channel 
10. CRE will call to Prospect Mobile number and confirm whether to buy a vehicle or not 
	- If not CRE needs to update the "Prospect Lost Reason" and update call status as "Closed" 
	- If Yes by Prospect and planned to buy after 2 months 
		- CRE should update "Likely Purchase Month" 
		- CRE should create Opportunity whose Likely Purchase Month <= 3 months 
		- CRE should Close the Prospect & generate an Opty against Prospect with Source of Prospect as "Dealer PSF Desk"
		- If Prospect is located outside the Territory of the Dealership, then CRE should close the Prospect by selecting a Prospect Lost Reason as "Out of Territory"

column1: Unable to proceed for Permanent Invoice Creation Error " Campaign Applicable is Mandatory" - (BU : PVBU)
column2:
Steps:
1. Active Position: DSAdmn
2. Login with credentials
3. Go to Site Map and select Orders
4. Search with Order Number
5. Click on Order Hyperlink
6. Click on Invoice View Tab
7. Click on Invoice Hyperlink
8. Scroll Down
9. Click on Related Campaigns View Tab
10. Check if any Campaigns are associated or not
11. If campaigns are associated, update Campaign Applicable Field as YES; otherwise, update it as NO and proceed for invoice creation without error
12. If Campaign Applicable Field is updated as YES, click on Validate Campaign Button to update the Scheme Eligibility Status as Valid
13. Navigate to Line Item Details View Tab
14. Click on New
15. Update/Pick Chassis Number
16. Proceed for Permanent Invoice Creation

column1: Unable to proceed for Permanent Invoice Creation Error " Concession OEM Amount Mismatch at Order with Concession Amount of Associated Schemes " - (BU : PVBU)
column2:
Steps:
1. Active Position: DSAdmn
2. Login with credentials
3. Go to Site Map and select Orders
4. Search with Order Number
5. Click on Order Hyperlink
6. Click on Invoice View Tab
7. Click on Invoice Hyperlink
8. Scroll Down
9. Click on Related Campaigns View Tab
10. Check if any campaigns are associated
11. If campaigns are associated, update Campaign Applicable Field as YES; otherwise, update it as NO and proceed for invoice creation without error
12. If Campaign Applicable Field is updated as YES, click on Validate Campaign Button to update the Scheme Eligibility Status as Valid
13. Click on Validate Campaign Button again to calculate the Total Concession Amount at Temporary Invoice Level
14. Copy the Total Concession Amount
15. Navigate to Sales Order Screen and go to Line Item View Tab
16. Update the copied Total Concession Amount in the Concession (OEM) Field
17. Click on Get Price
18. The value present in the Concession Field at the Order Level will be the final Concession Amount at the Invoice Level
19. Go to Invoice View Tab and click on Invoice Hyperlink
20. Scroll Down
21. Click on New
22. Select Chassis
23. Proceed for Permanent Invoice Creation

(Note: All campaigns must be in Valid Status. If any campaign status reflects as Invalid, follow Campaign Validation Steps. If the associated campaign is still not eligible, deassociate the invalid campaign and then proceed for invoice creation.)

column1: TD Unblocking
column2:
Steps to Request Unblocking of Chassis

 Active Position: CCA

1. Login to the system.
2. Navigate to Site Map.
3. Select Vehicles.
4. Click on All Vehicles Across Organization.
5. Search with Chassis Number.
6. Check the Physical Status of the Chassis:
   - If the Physical Status is "Test Drive Vehicle":
     1. Check if the respective SPOC person's approval is provided.
     2. If approval is provided:
        - Send an email to the Data Team.
        - Keep the Ticket Number in PEND 3RD PARTY until confirmation is received from the Data Team via email.
        - Once a response is received, check in CRM again whether the status is updated to "Available" and Physical Status as "In-Transit" or "Received-OK."

Email Format

- To: crmdatateam@tatamotors.com
- CC: CBSL-CRMSupport-Lead@tatamotors.com
- Subject: TD Unblocking - 'Request No'

Email Body:
```
Dear Team,

Kindly unblock the below-mentioned Chassis for retail as per attached approval.

BU -

Ticket No            Chassis No

Regards,
YOUR NAME,
CRM-DMS Support Team.
```

column1: Unable to proceed for Invoice Creation against STK Order Error " Source Location of Chasssis is not in proper Bucket"
column2:
Steps
1. Active Position: DSAdmn OR CCA
2. If only STK Order details are provided:
   1. Login to the system.
   2. Navigate to Site Map.
   3. Select Order.
   4. Click on Orders-Admin.
   5. Search with STK Order Number.
   6. Check if Order Status is "Shipped."
3. If the Order Status is not "Shipped":
   1. Active Position: DSAdmn.
   2. Login to the system.
   3. Navigate to Site Map.
   4. Select Order.
   5. Click on Inter Dealer Stock Transfer Shipping Tab.
   6. Search with STK Order Number.
   7. Check if Order Status is "Approved."
   8. Click on Line Items View Tab.
   9. Click on Process Shipment Tab.
   10. Order Status will be updated as "Shipped."
4. If an error popup states "Chassis is not in proper Bucket (On-Hand, Good). Kindly check with system admin":
   1. Escalate to the Concerned Team along with proper details, investigation, and error screenshots.
5. To check the Requestor Name of Ticket No if the division is present:
   1. Active Position: CCA.
   2. Login to the system.
   3. Navigate to Site Map.
   4. Go to Administration.
   5. Select Users.
   6. Click on Employees.
   7. Search with the copied User ID.
   8. Check in Position Pick Applet if the Admin Position is present.
   9. If the Admin Position is not present:
      1. Scroll down and click on Show More.
      2. Copy the Division Name from the Division Field.
   10. Navigate to Administration.
   11. Click on Group.
   12. Select Positions.
   13. Search with Division Name in Division Field (without pressing Enter).
   14. In the Position Field, search with *DSAdmn*.
   15. The Admin Position of the respective Division will reflect.
   16. Click on Last Name Pick Applet.
   17. Search with individual CCA User ID in the User ID Field on the left-hand side.
   18. Click Go.
   19. Click on the right-side arrow.
   20. Click on Cancel.
   21. The Admin Position will be assigned to your CCA User ID.
   22. Logout and then login again to reflect the Position in User Profile Reference Tab and proceed further.

column1: Unable to Add Expenses Due to " New " (+) Option is Disabled
column2:
Steps
1. Active Position: DSM
2. Login to the system.
3. Navigate to Site Map.
4. Select User Profile Reference.
5. Select the correct LOB based DSM Position.
6. Click on Change Position Button.
7. Navigate to Site Map.
8. Select Events.
9. Open the Simplified Events Screen.
10. Verify that the Event Name is reflected.
11. If the desired/user-provided Event Name is not reflected, click on the Right Forward Arrow (>) present at the right-hand corner after the 1 of 1 + symbol to navigate between created or approved events.
12. Check that the Event Plan Name Status is approved.
13. Scroll down to check that the Execution Date and Expense Status are blank.
14. Click on the New Button in the Expenses Tab.
15. Update the Expense Types and save the record (Note: TML Expense should be less than or equal to Approved Budget (TML)).
17. Update the Expense Status to "Sent for Approval."
18. After the Expense Status is approved, update the Execution Date to execute the event.
19. Once the Execution Date is punched, the Child Event Status will update to "Executed."
20. The status will be updated by DAM as "Executed - Validated by TML" at the last stage.

 Note: The Execution Date is the actual execution date of the event. If the current date is greater than the planned date and the execution date is blank, then the status will change to ?Delayed.?

21. If the New Button is disabled to add the Expense and no line item is visible, escalate to the Concerned Team along with proper details, investigation, and error screenshots.

 Note: The Execution Date is the actual execution date of the event. If the current date is greater than the planned date and the execution date is blank, then the status will change to ?Delayed.?

column1: Unable to place POTML Order Due to Error OR SAP Comments : " E : Order receipt/delivery not possible, credit customer blocked "
column2:
Steps

1. Active Position: DSAdmn
2. Login to the system.
3. Navigate to Site Map.
4. Select Order.
5. Click on Order again.
6. Search with the Sales Order No.
7. Click on the Payment Receipt View Tab.
8. Check if the Payment Receipt is created.
9. Ensure the Sales Order Status is "Booked."
10. Click on the Booking Details & Vehicle Allotment View Tab.
11. Scroll down and copy the UQ ID from the EDD Line Item.
12. Navigate to Vehicle Procurement.
13. Go to TML YF Orders.
14. Click on the New Button.
15. A POTML Order with Status "New" will be created.
16. Click on the Sales Order Pick Applet.
17. Select the Sales Order.
18. Click on the UQ ID Pick Applet.
19. Select the correct IQ ID.
20. Fill all the mandatory details at Order Details.
21. Add the line item with the VC No that needs to be ordered.
22. Only one line item can be added to YFPO, and the POTML requested VC number should match the Sales Order (YF) VC number.
23. Click on Submit For Approval.
24. The POTML Order Status will update to "Pending for Approval."
25. The "Approve to SAP" button will be enabled.
26. Click on the Approve to SAP Button.
27. The Order Status will be updated to "Order Placed," and the SAP Sales Order Number will generate and be punched in the SAP Order Number field.
28. If the error "E: Order receipt/delivery not possible, credit customer blocked" is reflecting when clicking on the Approve to SAP Button, escalate to the Concerned Team along with proper details, investigation, and error screenshots.

column1: Parts not Shipped in Job Card or OTC Order or any other Order.

5. Click on the Pick Ticket hyperlink.  
6. Click on Process Shipment.  
7. If the Part is still not Shipped, change the status of the Pick Ticket from Open to Closed.  
8. Select the Pending Parts in Job Card Parts or OTC Order.  
9. Go to Edit and then Change Records.  
10. Select "Status" in Field.  
11. Enter Value "Shipped."  
12. Click OK and save the changes. The Parts will get Shipped now.

column1: Pick Ticket is not generated for Part Shipment in Job Card, OTC or any other Order.
column2:
Steps:  
1. If the Pick Ticket is not getting generated against the Part in Job Card and OTC Order, check the Part in the Source Inventory Location to ensure it is not 0 On Hand.  
2. Check if any Reserve Quantity is present against the Part; there should be none.

column1: Unable to Enter Part in Job Card, OTC or any other Order.
column2:
Steps:  
1. Active Position: DPM.

column1: Part Receiving : SAP Invoice is not reflecting in Receiving. (Non CRM)
column2:
Active Position: DPM  
Steps:  
1. Check for the SAP Invoice in Receiving -> Spare Purchase Line Item - Editable.  
2. Query with SAP Invoice Number.  
3. If the invoice is not reflecting, navigate to Accounting Extracts -> Spare Purchase Header.  
4. Query with SAP Invoice Number.  
5. Copy the Non-CRM SAP Order.  
6. Navigate to Purchase Order -> Non-CRM Orders In SAP.  
7. Query with the copied Non-CRM SAP Order.  
8. Verify that the order status is "Order Placed."  
9. Check that the Owner Position carefully matches the DPM of the respective correct division.  
10. Ensure the Active Position and Owner Position are the same.  
11. Confirm that the Owner Position should not be editable.  
12. Navigate again to Receiving -> Spare Purchase Line Item - Editable.  
13. Query with the SAP Invoice Number.  
14. The SAP Invoice Number will now be reflecting.

column1: Part Receiving : SAP Invoice is not reflecting in Receiving. (SAP Order)
column2:
Active Position: DPM  
Steps:  
1. Check for the SAP Invoice in Receiving -> Spare Purchase Line Item - Editable.  
2. Query with SAP Invoice Number.  
3. If the invoice is not reflecting, navigate to Accounting Extracts -> Spare Purchase Header.  
4. Query with SAP Invoice Number.  
5. Copy the SAP Order Number.  
6. Navigate to CV: Purchase Order -> SAP Purchase Orders or PV: SAP PVBU Purchase Orders -> Miscellaneous Orders.  
7. Query with the copied SAP Order.  
8. Verify that the order status is "Order Placed."  
9. Click on the SAP Order hyperlink.  
10. Ensure the received line item is present against the part line item.  
11. Check for the pending quantity against any part in the line item.  
12. If pending quantity is present, escalate the ticket with proper mentioning.

column1: Unable to Enter Prolife Core Part in OTC Order
column2:
navigation step: Active Position: DPM

1. Go to Site Map.  
2. Click on Order.  
3. Select Job Cards.  
4. Query with JC.  
5. Check Job Card Parts and note the Source Inventory Location.  
6. Look for Prolife Part Line Item.  
7. Check the Core Part in the "Prolife Core Part" column.  
8. Click on the Ship Pick Ticket hyperlink.  
9. Check the Prolife Part in the Pick Ticket.  
10. Check the Serial Number (right bottom).  
11. Go to Site Map.  
12. Click on Inventory.  
13. Select All Inventory Locations.  
14. Click on the noted Inventory Location hyperlink.  
15. Query and check the Core Part On Hand Qty (must be at least 1).  
16. Go to Site Map.  
17. Click on Order.  
18. Select OTC Sales.  
19. Query with OTC Order.  
20. Toggle from OTC Sales to OTC Sales Details.  
21. Check the Order Status (must be New).  
22. Check the Sub Type (must be Prolife).  
23. Check the Parts Price List (must be TMCV Prolife Core Price List).  
24. Check the Source Inventory Location (must be noted).  
25. Toggle back from OTC Sales Details to OTC Sales.  
26. Click on New in Line Item for adding Core Part.  
27. Add the Core Part in "Part Number".  
28. Pick the Source Inventory Location that was noted.  
29. Pick the JC in "Job Card Number".  
30. Pick the Prolife Part in "FG Part".  
31. Pick the Serial Number in "FG Serial Number".  
32. Pick the Price List "TMCV Prolife Core Price List".  
33. Save.  
34. Click on Get Price.  
35. Fulfill for generating Pick Ticket.  

Enter the details in the below chronological order:

Core Part
Source Inventory Location
Job Card
FG Part
FG Serial
Price List

If FG Part or FG Serial is not reflecting after following the above navigation, then escalate the same with all the details mentioned.

column1: Part De-Reserve
column2:
navigation step: 
Active Position: DPM
1. Go to Site Map.
2. Click on Inventory.
3. Select Inventory Locations.
4. Click on the Inventory Location hyperlink.
5. Check and note the Reserved Part Quantity.
6. Go to Site Map.
7. Click on Order.
8. Select De Allocate.
9. Query with Part in the Part Number column, Inventory Location in the Inventory Location column, "Allocate" in Type, and "Open" in Status.
10. Check and click on any one line item (might be JC/OTC Order, note down the same).
11. Toggle from DeAllocate List to DeAllocate Form.
12. Click on De-Allocate (part should be de-reserved).
13. If any error reflects:
    1. Toggle from DeAllocate Form to DeAllocate List.
    2. Click on the Pick Ticket hyperlink of the same line item.
    3. Delete the picked quantity by clicking on the Menu Icon, then select Delete Record.
    4. Click on Process Shipment (part should be de-reserved).
14. Check the part in the Inventory Location again.
15. If still not reserved, navigate to the order that was already noted in the De Allocate screen.
16. If it is a JC, then navigate to Job Card Parts; if it is an OTC Order, then parts will be directly visible.
17. Go to Site Map.
18. Click on Order.
19. Select Job Cards or OTC/CPOTC Order.
20. Under the Actions section where Pick Tickets are visible, click on the Allocate Pick Ticket line.
21. Click on the Actions Menu (Settings Menu).
22. Scroll down and click on De-Allocate (part should be de-reserved).
23. Pick Ticket with type "De-Allocate" will be visible in Line Item, meaning that the part is de-reserved.
24. Check the Reserved Quantity of the part again in the Inventory.

If after following all the steps mentioned, the part is still not de-reserved, ask the user to provide APM approval and escalate the same with proper mentioning and error screenshots.

column1: Core Part not reflecting in Inventory Location
column2:
navigation step: 
Active Position: DPM
1. Go to Site Map.
2. Click on Inventory.
3. Select Inventory Locations.
4. Click on the Inventory Location hyperlink.
5. Check Part Quantity (On Hand).
6. Check the Stock Ledger with Core Part:
   1. Go to Site Map.
   2. Click on Inventory Transaction.
   3. Select Stock Ledger.
   4. Query with Core Part.
   5. Look for "PRO-IN" transaction with JC in the Order column.
7. Check and validate the Core Part against the JC:
   1. Go to Site Map.
   2. Click on Order.
   3. Select Job Cards.
   4. Query with JC.
   5. Click on Job Card Parts.
   6. Query with Prolife Part.
   7. Check the Core Part.
   8. Check the JC Closure Date.
   9. Check the JC Invoice Date.

The JC Closure Date and JC Invoice Date must be the same date. If mismatched, then the Core Part is not inwarded and will not reflect in the inventory. Prolife TSM approval is needed for inwarding the Core Part because it is not inwarded due to the mismatch of JC Closure Date and JC Invoice Date.

column1: HSN Code & Tax Slab % not reflecting against Part
column2:
navigation step: 
Active Position: DPM
1. Go to Site Map.
2. Click on Pricing Administration.
3. Select Parts Sales Price List.
4. Click on SPARES PRICE LIST hyperlink.
5. Query with Part Number.
6. Check the HSN Code and Tax Slab.
7. Go to Site Map.
8. Click on Products.
9. Select Parts Master.
10. Query with Part Number.
11. Only HSN Code can be checked here; for Tax Slab, follow the above navigation.

If the HSN Code and Tax Slab are blank against the part, take the HSN Code and Tax Slab % from the user provided by APM/Business and escalate the same with all the details.

column1:
Dealer not reflecting in Product Location against Digi-VOR Order
Error "E : Qty field is blank/No Schedule lines item found while creating Sales Order" while placing the Digi-VOR Order
column2:
Steps
Active Position: DPM
1. Go to Site Map.

3. Select VOR Order.
4. Query with Digi-VOR Order.
5. Toggle from Digi-VOR to Digi-VOR Detail.

column1: Unable to Receive Parts against CPPUR Order
column2:
Steps
Active Position: DPM (Sender)

1. Go to Site Map.

3. Select Spares Purchase Line Items - Editable.
4. Query with CPOTC Invoice Number in the SAP Invoice Number column.
5. Follow the parts receiving process as usual.
6. If the Invoice Number is not reflecting, navigate through Purchase Orders:
   1. Go to Site Map.
   2. Click on Purchase Orders.

   6. Check the status; it should be Order Placed.

column1: How to find out Live Green Form, Yellow Form & Retail data in MyLead App
column2:
Steps

1. Login with DSE User Id.
2. Go to MyLead Apps.
3. Access My Lead Dashboard Screen.
4. Click on the Performance Tab.
5. To see monthly performance, click on "Green Form Created," "Yellow Form Created," and "Retail."

column1: Changes in Lead Classification
column2:
Steps

1. Go to MyLeads App.
2. Access Opty Creation Screens.
3. Update Purchase Date.
4. Save as Draft or Submit.
5. Navigate to My Leads Search Screen.
6. Search with Last Name and Mobile No.
7. Update Created Date From and To.
8. Select Lead Classification from the drop-down box.

column1: TMA Sourcing Opty Creation for Customer Type-Exchange
column2:
Steps

1. Set Customer Type to "Exchange."
2. Specify Exchange Vehicle Type.
3. Validate NTML and Registration No.
4. Create New NTML Vehicle.
5. Submit.

column1: Dashboard (GF, Booking YF, Retail -> Current Month -> Achieved vs Target)
column2:
Navigation Steps:

1. Go to Dashboard.
2. Select Life GF/Booking YF/Retail to view GF/YF/Retail.
3. Check at Dealership & Division level as per hierarchy (DSM, TL & CA Level).
4. Compare Achieved vs Target.

column1: Dashboard Missed Activities
column2:
Navigation Steps:

1. Click on Missed Activities on the Dashboard.
2. View TSM information at the Dealership level.
3. For the next level, click to see Outlet level numbers.
4. This view is similar to the one at the Dealership level.

column1: Product-wise Pipeline Report
column2:
Navigation Steps:

1. Go to the Dashboard.
2. Select Product Pipeline.
3. Search for Individual Name, CRM Id, Dealership, or Outlet Name.
4. View the Product Pipeline information.

column1: My Team Views Report
column2:
Navigation Steps:

1. Go to the Dashboard.
2. Click on My Team.
3. Select Division to view TSM at SM and TL levels.
4. Click on TL for TSM view at CA level.

column1: TD delayed beyond 3 days Report
column2:
TD delayed beyond 3 days count to be present at each level i.e. Dealership, Division, SM, TL & CA Level. Header to be changed to TD delayed beyond 3 days.
   - Note: Here TL view is shown

column1: Performance Report
column2:
Navigation Steps:

1. Go to the Dashboard.
2. Click on Performance.
3. Click on GF Created/YF Created/Retail/Conversation Ratio.
4. Click on Filter.
5. Search with Dealership, Division, and SM/TL.
6. Click on Search.
7. Check the Month-wise Achieved vs Target Report.
